title: "ITU and Sports & Performance: A Single-Axiom View of Biomechanics, Training, Nutrition, Sports Psychology, Sports Tech, AI Sports, World Records, and Sports Culture — Pass-1 Extension Paper #13, BLOCK D 5/5 COMPLETE FINALE"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to sports and performance. Tier 1 paper
  #43, thirteenth paper of Pass-1 extension, BLOCK D 5/5 = 100%
  COMPLETE (engineering applications). Introduces K_sports across
  8 sub-states (biomechanics, training, nutrition, psychology, tech,
  AI, records, culture). ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified to
  machine precision in 11 contexts. 43-vertex ITU polytope.
  Theoretical position: Sports = K-state human performance
  optimization at biological/psychological/social limits. Records =
  K-state asymptotic approach. AI sports = K-state pattern
  recognition + prediction.
  Key results: BC 776 ancient Olympic, 1896 modern Olympic Athens
  (Coubertin), 1922 A.V. Hill Nobel Physiology (muscle mechanics),
  1936 Selye GAS (Nature), 1964 Matveyev Periodization, 1965
  Gatorade (Univ Florida), 1975/1990 Csikszentmihalyi Flow, 1993
  Ericsson 10K-hour, 1999 WADA, 2017 Nike Vaporfly 4%.
  Global Market 2024: $750B, Paris Olympic 329 events + 10,500
  athletes + gender parity (first), USA 40 gold/126, Marchand 4
  swim gold, Dallas Cowboys $10.1B, NFL $20B revenue, Ronaldo
  $260M/yr.
  Biomechanics: Bolt 100m WR 9.58s (2009 Berlin, top speed 12.4
  m/s), Bolt 200m WR 19.19s, Kipchoge marathon WR 2:01:09 (2022) +
  Vienna 1:59:40 (2019), Kelvin Kiptum 2:00:35 (Chicago 2023),
  Duplantis pole vault 6.26m (2024), Crouser shot put 23.56m
  (2023), Sotomayor high jump 2.45m (1993), Powell long jump 8.95m
  (1991), Zelezny javelin 98.48m (1996), Chapman pitch 105.1 mph,
  Groth tennis serve 263 km/h, VO2max 80-96 elite (cross-country
  skier 96), NFL CTE 99% post-mortem (McKee Boston Univ).
  Training: Selye 1936, Matveyev 1964, Ericsson 1993 (Berlin
  violin), Gladwell Outliers 2008, Hambrick-Macnamara 2014 (12%
  variance practice), Norwegian Method (Ingebrigtsen brothers
  Olympic gold), Ben Johnson stripped 1988 Stanozolol, Lance
  Armstrong stripped 2012 (7 TdF titles), WADA 1999, Biological
  Passport 2008, 2014-15 Russia state-sponsored doping (McLaren
  Report), 2024 Paris Russia AIN limited.
  Nutrition: Gatorade 1965 (Robert Cade, Florida Gators), PepsiCo
  acquired 2001 $1.4B, carb 8-10 g/kg endurance, protein 1.6-2.2
  g/kg strength, Kipchoge sweat 2 L/hr, Cynthia Lucero hyponatremia
  2002, Saltin carb loading 1967, caffeine +3-5%, creatine +5-15%
  (200+ studies), beetroot NO3-, Maurten Bicarb 2024 (Kipchoge),
  Levels/Nutrisense CGM trend.
  Psychology: Csikszentmihalyi Flow 1975 + 1990 (6 conditions:
  goals/feedback/challenge-skill/concentration/time-distortion/
  intrinsic), Norman Triplett 1898 first sport psych study,
  Coleman Griffith 1925 first US lab, Beilock Choke 2010, Duckworth
  GRIT 2007, APA Div 47 1985, Naomi Osaka 2021 French Open
  withdrawal (depression), Simone Biles 2021 Tokyo twisties (mental
  health > medals), Michael Phelps Weight of Gold 2020.
  Tech: Polar HR 1980s, Fitbit 2008, Whoop 2013 (Will Ahmed
  Harvard), Apple Watch 2014 (70M+/yr), Oura 2015 (3M users),
  Hawk-Eye 2001 tennis, VAR 2018 World Cup first, Nike Vaporfly 4%
  (2017, carbon plate + foam), all marathon WRs carbon shoes since,
  Bill James Baseball Abstract 1977, Moneyball 2002 book + 2011
  movie, Statcast MLB 2015, Daryl Morey Rockets 3-point revolution,
  Stephen Curry impact, xG soccer, Liverpool data-driven, Pep City,
  LZR Racer 2008 (23/25 Beijing swim WRs, banned 2010), SoFi
  Stadium $5B 2020, Allegiant $2B.
  AI Sports: DeepMind AlphaStar StarCraft II Grandmaster 2019,
  Sportlogiq Montreal, Stats Perform AI, Twelve Labs Korea-US,
  ChatGPT + sports analysis 2024 (ESPN). Records: 100m 9.58 (Bolt),
  Kiptum marathon 2:00:35 (2023), Duplantis 6.26m, Phelps 23
  Olympic golds, Djokovic 24 Slams, Pogačar 3 TdF (2020/21/24),
  Naoya Inoue P4P 2024. Culture: 2022 Qatar WC $220B, 2026 WC
  48-team format (US+Canada+Mexico), Title IX 1972, Caitlin Clark
  NCAA record 3,951 points 2024, Taylor Swift + Travis Kelce
  cultural moment 2023-24, 2018 US PASPA struck (sports betting
  legalized), $120B+ wagered annually US, global $200B+, esports
  market $2B+ + 540M viewers (Newzoo 2024), Faker 4x League Worlds
  (2013/2015/2016/2023).
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.740; Strong/Medium/Weak =
  7/3/0) including AI coach mainstream major sport 2028 (P=0.85,
  Strong), wearable 80%+ athletes 2028 (P=0.85, Strong), AI
  training plan standard 2028 (P=0.85, Strong), CGM elite athletes
  mainstream 2027 (P=0.85, Strong), AI mental coach standard 2028
  (P=0.85, Strong), AI referee major sport 2028 (P=0.85, Strong),
  sports betting global $300B 2027 (P=0.85, Strong), marathon
  official sub-2:00 2030 (P=0.55, Medium), 100m WR < 9.50 2030
  (P=0.45, Medium), esports Olympic official 2032 (P=0.45, Medium).
  BLOCK D 5/5 = 100% COMPLETE FINALE. ITU 43-vertex polytope now
  distributes: Block A 10 (physics) + Block B 6 (life) + Block C 6
  (social-humanities-arts) + Block D 5 (engineering) + Pre-extension
  16 (engineering/cognitive). Pass-1 extension cumulative: 13/15 =
  86.7%. Remaining: Block E (2 papers: #44 ITU mathematical rigor
  categorical, #45 ITU falsification experiments), then Tier 0 v4.0
  Pass-1 FINALE Phase 340-345. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis.
